Description: Levy Retreats purpose is to see people whole and renewed diligently to ensure many generations benefit from attending.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: Twelve years ago, Edith Levy began facilitating a program that dealt with healing in a way that few had seen done before. With God as the center, this program has seen thousands of lives renewed and restored. What began with a 12-week curriculum, Edith sculpted to a 4-day format with well needed updates. Over the past year as Levy Retreats tested the waters, it became very evident that the need was greater than ever but a facility to fulfill that need was greatly needed.  Currently, they have found a property that would perfectly suit the needs of the retreat. They are eager to allow those on the waiting list to begin the program and have reached out to hundreds of churches, counselors, and church staff to continue reaching those in need. Their only hurdle now is to find the funding to purchase the property.   The curriculum inquires of individuals:  Can You Relate?   * I can’t stand to be alone.    * I am a perfectionist.    * I feel unloved and ignored.    * I feel depressed if I can’t gain the approval of others.    * I over-eat often to feel good.    * Growing up, rules were used to punish, not teach.    * I can’t say “no” when I am asked to do a favor.    * I am out of control.    * My emotions are controlled and repressed.    * I have been sexually abused.    * Don’t speak, don’t feel, don’t trust.    * I feel angry and don’t know why.    * I am hopeless, lost, and feel dead inside.    * I feel I have potential, but I just can’t do it.    * I don’t feel like God could possibly love me .    Topics discussed include:   The Family System   • Family Roles   • Effects of Childhood Trauma   • Unhealthy Relationships   • The Cycle of Abuse   • Shame and Guilt   • The Process of Change   • Forgiveness   • Breaking the Cycle for the Next Generation     Their purpose is to see people whole and renewed and they will work diligently to ensure many generations benefit from attending.

Full Description: A dermatologist is a medical doctor, earning an MD (Doctor of Medicine) or a DO (Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine) license that allows the individual to specialize in treating many of the physical features that make you human. Acne is the most common skin disease in the world — 80 percent of all people experience an acne breakout at some point in their lives, often during the teenage years. Acne is a skin condition in which the pores become clogged with sebum (oil) and dead skin cells. These clogs are referred to as comedones or blackheads and whiteheads. Propionibacterium acnes bacteria found on the skin can becomes trapped in these clogged pores. As the bacteria thrive on the sebum and pustule begins to form. Over time this triggers an inflammatory response from and a deep tender cystic lesion may form, which may eventually lead to follicle rupture if untreated. Eczema, also called atopic dermatitis, is one of the diagnoses you get when you have red spots on your skin that become inflamed and itchy. A top dermatologist in Manhattan recognizes the symptoms right away and recommends the best treatment for eczema based on your current health and medical history. A chronic yet routine skin condition in people over the age of 30, rosacea generally manifests itself as the extreme visibility of red blood vessels in your cheeks, nose, and forehead. It often appears in flare-ups lasting for several weeks or even months, only to then temporarily disappear into remission. Unless you have it treated, it will continue to recur. Psoriasis is one of the more misunderstood skin disorders today. It’s a condition where your skin cells’ life cycle changes so that they regenerate much more rapidly. In fact, skin cells multiply 10 times faster with psoriasis. As a result, the cells build up on the surface of your skin.

Actresses and models swear by Lindy and Naturally Lindy products, both for regular healthy skin maintenance and for emergency problems and flair-ups. And Naturally Lindy products are so healing that cancer patients are using Naturally Lindy products to deal with treatment side effects such as severe acne, called " acne-form " rashes. Naturally Lindy skin products revitalize and balance your skin, leaving you with a healthy glow. From acne to aging and from season to season, Naturally Lindy can provide whatever your skin needs to become its healthy best.

Full Description: Wazetrip.com is a startup located in the east side of the great Seattle area in the United States. It is found in 2013.  Wazetrip is striving to provide great benefits to both travelers and hotel booking partners. We introduced a number of innovations to significantly improve the hotel booking experience. Why travelers should choose wazetrip.com? The mission of Wazetrip is – one click to find the desired hotels: low price, high quality, great location, etc.  Study shows that in US travelers take an average of 3.5 hours to find and book a hotel. The time can be even longer in some other countries. Although there are some booking sites to help making the process easier, travelers still spend a lot of time on things like comparing prices from multiple sites, looking up addresses on map tools, etc. The question is can we have a place where travelers can easily find every information they need so that they can make the booking much faster and smoother? Wazetrip.com provides an all-in-one solution to solve these problems. Here is the typical process of hotel booker to use wazetrip. 1. Find the best location  If hotel booker already have stored travel plans and activities in their TripIt account, Google calendar or Outlook calendar, wazetrip let hotel booker to import their travel activities onto map by just clicking a button. Once the travel activities are on map, hotel booker can easily see which hotels are closer to their travel activities and make best decision.  If hotel booker don’t have stored travel plans, they can easily pin their desired visiting address in our address bar onto map and see which hotel is closer to it.  No travel activities decided yet? That is OK. Wazetrip can help you. Our categorized P.O.I (point of interest) will show 10,000+ popular visiting points in U.S. Traveler can decide which point to visit by looking at the reviews, photos etc. The distance information to the P.O.I from any hotel on map will pop up when you click any hotel.  2. Find the best quality As other meta search website, wazetrip provides hotel and room photos, TripAdvisor reviews, amenities, policies information too, but in a more organized way.  In addition, our street view on map provide hotel booker an interactive view of the hotel. For 50% of hotels, wazetrip can provide indoor 3D view to let hotel booker feel they were really walking in the hotel.  3. Find the lowest price  Wazetrip searches 200,000+ hotels through dozens hotel booking sites. It is guaranteed to find the lowest price hotels that meet your needs.  Hotel price fluctuate as travel time changes. Wazetrip provides a trend chart in next 9 months for every hotel to let hotel bookers to find the best time to have lowest price.  Whether you are traveling for business or personal leisure, you can always find great hotels through wazetrip.com!

But we’ve noticed is that we usually visit more museums, galleries and festivals abroad than right here, in their own city. When we’re in travel mode, we put in the time and effort to plan, but at home? Not so much… When travelling, we put in that time and effort, because we don’t want to miss out on the cool stuff – who knows when we’ll be back again. But back in their hometown, we think of it as a hassle. It’s all going to be there next week. Or next year … And so time goes by, and we keep on missing out on lots of cool stuff going on. They believe that planning a free day should be fun, simple and really quick. Just tell us what kind of fun you’re looking for – family & kids, off the beaten path, or popular – and we’ll show you some of the best options in the city today – including street festivals, exhibitions, shows, markets and other activities. Choose something, and then The Funday Genie does the rest of the work for you. Their smart algorithm will find more stuff for you to do in that area, and put it all into a smart day’s plan. This plan takes into consideration opening hours, proximity, available transportation modes, and the user’s preferences. You can save this funday, send to your email, easily access from your smartphone, and share on your Facebook wall.

Full Description: Aspromonte Marketing based in Cherry Hill, New Jersey is a rapidly growing marketing and sales company with a simple concept – operate with integrity, deliver high sales volume for clients, and provide growth opportunities to employees. It’s because of these straight forward standards that they are growing at such a rate that is uncommon for most businesses. Read on to learn more about the no-nonsense business philosophies that are proving to be a winning strategy at Aspromonte Marketing. Nick Aspromonte, President of Aspromonte Marketing has a sports background in baseball and football. His experience playing competitive sports for most of his life has without a doubt shaped the way he thinks when it comes to business. Aspromonte has a very direct coaching style with his employees which allows everyone to know exactly what is expected of them. For anyone who has worked in a fog of grey areas before, it’s actually quite refreshing to know exactly what the boss is looking for. He also holds the team to a high standard of performance. And not just in achieving a certain level of results, but in taking personal accountability for their actions as well as doing the right thing at all times. When it comes to growing in a lucrative business career, Aspromonte says, “We as millennials need to change the way we think.” His vision is much different than joining the work force, putting in 30 years with a company and then living off of your pensions and social security. “In order to be financially stable you have to put in the work now and build for the future,” he added. It’s this way of thinking that truly shapes the entrepreneurial spirit of Aspromonte Marketing. Employees are challenged to think outside the box and push the envelope when it comes to setting personal and professional goals within the company. So what do you get when have a very candid business leader, a company full of competitive individuals and you provide them with a merit based internal advancement structure? Satisfied clients, happy employees and an ever-expanding company. Learn more about Aspromonte Marketing in Cherry Hill, NJ by calling 856-320-2050.

Description: I help companies to generate more leads and sales with an intelligent, well-executed PPC campaigns and website design
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: My name is Mathew Pinelli and I have been working with Google Ads (formerly Adwords), Yahoo, and Bing since 2005 I am Google Certified and a Google Partner. Presenting yourself and your qualities over the internet is much harder than in person, so hopefully, this portrays who you would be hiring as best as it can. I am a father and husband living in New York. As I said, I have been working with Google Ads, Bing/Yahoo, and social media ads as far back as 2005. I started using these types of ads to make money on my own promoting affiliate programs. I have worked for various agencies on a part-time remote basis until I started my dream job as a police officer here in New York. Since becoming a police officer, I have always kept up with digital marketing promoting various products and services that work on during my days off. In 2012, I decided that I wanted to do something more rewarding and started working with small to medium businesses with budgets anywhere from $500/month to $20,000/month. I have worked with dentists, doctors, physical therapists, lawyers, dumpster rentals, plumbers, roofers, tour agencies, travel agencies, exterminators, car dealerships, etc. You name it I’ve pretty much worked with someone in that industry along the way. Now I know you must be thinking, “Why would I hire someone who already has a full-time job and a family that will probably not give me the attention I deserve?” Great question. With my current work schedule, I work mostly late at night and I work my 40 hours in four days. Then I am off for four days. So that usually means I am off around 15 days a month. During those days (and before work) I live, breathe, and eat everything paid search. I assure you I would not be running this business if I thought for one second I wouldn’t give you your money’s worth. Running a business has many moving parts that all need to be monitored by yourself or qualified employees you trust. You could hire an in-house internet “guy” or “gal” right out of college with no experience to save some money; Or you could hire someone with years of experience and pay for his expertise.  There are costs to advertise your job opening or hiring a recruiter to find you the perfect employee. Then there’s the salary, benefits, employment taxes, space in your office, new equipment, and of course paid time off. At the end of the article, one entrepreneur calculates that the cost of a managed employee costs 2.7 times the base salary they’re hired at. Notice I said a managed employee. If you’re hiring a web/marketing person are you going to hire an even better one to manage him or delegate his work to one of your current managers? Or do you plan on overseeing the work of someone in which you aren’t well educated in what they do?I always tell my clients to concentrate on being the best at what they do. Delegate the work you're not experienced into qualified professionals. Hiring someone new in your business isn’t always a bad thing. You’re expanding and giving someone an opportunity to make your business better. Plus you're helping the local economy. If these things are the driving force behind your hiring in-house then I wish you the best with your new employee. Going the outsourced route with Matt PPC is the smart move in this situation. Our rate is our rate and is usually one-fourth of what you would expect to pay a full-time PPC marketer with my experience. We have all the resources at our fingertips to start right away…….weekends and nights included. We never stop working to improve your online presence. That’s something you will never get with a 9-5er
